# MIYAR 2.0 — Intelligent Intake System

> **Vision:** Stop asking developers to fill 50 form fields. Let them dump what they have — images, PDFs, voice, URLs, text. MIYAR translates it into structured [ProjectInputs](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/shared/miyar-types.ts#36-102). The form becomes a review checkpoint, not a data entry burden.

---

## The Core Insight

```
Today:       Developer → 50 form fields → Score
MIYAR 2.0:   Developer → freeform assets → AI translation → form review → Score
```

**Every engine, every router, every scoring function stays identical.** The [ProjectInputs](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/shared/miyar-types.ts#36-102) contract is sacred. What changes is how that contract gets populated — and the developer's experience of doing so.

---

## Deep Codebase Wiring Audit

### How Data Flows Today

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["ProjectForm.tsx<br/>7-step wizard, ~50 fields"] -->|"trpc.project.create"| B["project.ts router<br/>projectInputSchema"]
    B -->|"stores in DB"| C["projects table<br/>42 columns"]
    C -->|"projectToInputs()"| D["ProjectInputs struct<br/>shared/miyar-types.ts"]
    D --> E["scoring.ts + five-lens.ts<br/>5-dimension MIYAR Score"]
    D --> F["normalization.ts<br/>Derived multipliers"]
    D --> G["explainability.ts<br/>Why scores are what they are"]
    D --> H["sensitivity.ts<br/>What-if analysis"]
    D --> I["scenario.ts<br/>Alternative configurations"]
    D --> J["design-brief.ts<br/>7-section AI brief"]
    D --> K["ai-design-advisor.ts<br/>Per-space recommendations"]
    D --> L["visual-gen.ts<br/>Mood board + renders"]
    D --> M["pdf-report.ts<br/>Board-ready exports"]
    D --> N["bias-detector.ts<br/>Anchoring/optimism alerts"]
    D --> O["roi.ts + economics router<br/>Platform ROI"]
```

### Files That Consume [ProjectInputs](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/shared/miyar-types.ts#36-102) (19 engines)

| Engine | What It Needs From Inputs |
|--------|--------------------------|
| [scoring.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/scoring.ts) | All 50 fields → composite score |
| [five-lens.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/five-lens.ts) | SA/FF/MP/DS/ER dimension calculations |
| [normalization.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/normalization.ts) | Scale band, budget class, derived multipliers |
| [explainability.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/explainability.ts) | Score drivers + penalty explanations |
| [sensitivity.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/sensitivity.ts) | Variable perturbation for what-if |
| [scenario.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/scenario.ts) | Override subsets for comparisons |
| [design-brief.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/design-brief.ts) | Style, tier, location → 7-section brief |
| [ai-design-advisor.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/design/ai-design-advisor.ts) | Per-space Gemini recommendations |
| [visual-gen.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/visual-gen.ts) | Prompt context for image generation |
| [pdf-report.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/pdf-report.ts) | All fields for board-ready exports |
| [bias-detector.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/bias/bias-detector.ts) | Detects unrealistic optimism |
| [area-utils.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/area-utils.ts) | GFA calculations |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **None of these engines change.** The AI Intake Engine outputs the same [ProjectInputs](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/shared/miyar-types.ts#36-102) struct. The form still validates manually. The scoring engine receives identical data.

