## Proposed Architecture

### Three Paths, One Destination

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Path 1: Talk to MIYAR"
        A1["Drop files<br/>Paste URLs<br/>Type/speak vision"] --> B1
    end
    subgraph "Path 2: Expert Mode"
        A2["7-step form<br/>(existing)"] --> C["ProjectInputs"]
    end
    subgraph "Path 3: Quick Brief"
        A3["Voice note / paragraph<br/>+ AI fills rest"] --> B1
    end
    B1["AI Intake Engine<br/>(Gemini multimodal)"] --> C
    C --> D["Review Form<br/>(always checkpoint)"]
    D --> E["Scoring Engine<br/>(unchanged)"]
```

### New Components

---

#### 1. Schema: `project_assets` Table

```sql
-- NEW TABLE: permanent asset storage per project
CREATE TABLE project_assets (
  id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  projectId INT NOT NULL,           -- FK to projects
  organizationId INT NOT NULL,
  assetType ENUM('image','pdf','audio','video','url','text_note') NOT NULL,
  fileName VARCHAR(500),
  fileUrl TEXT,                      -- S3 signed URL or external URL
  fileKey VARCHAR(512),             -- S3 key for internal files
  fileMimeType VARCHAR(128),
  fileSizeBytes INT,
  aiExtractionResult JSON,          -- what Gemini extracted from this asset
  aiContributions JSON,             -- which ProjectInputs fields this asset populated
  uploadedAt TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  uploadedBy INT
);
```

> [!NOTE]
> Assets are stored permanently on the project — not just used for form-filling. They become the project's evidence base referenced by design briefs, investor summaries, and reports.

---

#### 2. Engine: `server/engines/intake/ai-intake-engine.ts` [NEW]

Pure function pattern (consistent with all existing engines):

```typescript
interface IntakeAsset {
  type: 'image' | 'pdf' | 'audio' | 'video' | 'url' | 'text_note';
  url: string;
  mimeType?: string;
  textContent?: string;  // for URLs: scraped content; for text_note: raw text
}

interface IntakeResult {
  suggestedInputs: Partial<ProjectInputs>;  // AI-populated fields
  confidence: Record<string, 'high' | 'medium' | 'low'>;  // per-field confidence
  reasoning: Record<string, string>;  // why each field was set
  extractedInsights: {
    detectedStyle?: string;
    detectedMaterials?: string[];
    detectedBrands?: string[];
    detectedTier?: string;
    detectedTypology?: string;
    floorPlanAnalysis?: FloorPlanAnalysis;
    supplierInfo?: { name: string; url: string; materials: string[] }[];
  };
  warnings: string[];
}

// Main function — processes all assets and returns field suggestions
async function processIntakeAssets(
  assets: IntakeAsset[],
  existingInputs?: Partial<ProjectInputs>
): Promise<IntakeResult>
```

**Key design decisions:**
- Calls `invokeLLM` with multimodal content (images + PDFs + text)
- Uses `outputSchema` to force Gemini into a typed JSON response matching [ProjectInputs](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/shared/miyar-types.ts#36-102) fields
- Reuses [analyzeFloorPlan()](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/design/floor-plan-analyzer.ts#89-198) from [floor-plan-analyzer.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/design/floor-plan-analyzer.ts) when PDFs/images of floor plans are detected
- Each field gets a confidence level — UI shows green (high), yellow (medium), red (low)
- Returns reasoning per field — so the review form can show "This was set because your mood board shows Japandi-style interiors"

---

#### 3. Engine: `server/engines/intake/url-scraper.ts` [NEW]

Handles supplier/competitor URL extraction:

```typescript
async function scrapeSupplierUrl(url: string): Promise<{
  supplierName: string;
  products: { name: string; category: string; priceRange?: string }[];
  materialTier: string;
  sourcingOrigin: string;
}>
```

Reuses concepts from existing ingestion connectors ([server/engines/ingestion/crawler.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/crawler.ts)) but tailored for single-URL extraction.

---

#### 4. Router: `server/routers/intake.ts` [NEW]

```typescript
intakeRouter = router({
  // Upload assets and get AI suggestions
  processAssets: orgProcedure
    .input(z.object({
      projectId: z.number().optional(),  // existing project or new
      assets: z.array(assetSchema),
    }))
    .mutation(async ({ input, ctx }) => {
      // 1. Store assets in project_assets table
      // 2. Call processIntakeAssets() engine
      // 3. Return IntakeResult
    }),

  // Get upload URL for file
  getUploadUrl: orgProcedure
    .input(z.object({ fileName: z.string(), contentType: z.string() }))
    .mutation(async ({ input }) => {
      // Generate presigned S3 upload URL
    }),

  // Chat-style interaction for refining suggestions
  refineWithChat: orgProcedure
    .input(z.object({
      projectId: z.number(),
      message: z.string(),
      currentInputs: z.record(z.any()),
    }))
    .mutation(async ({ input }) => {
      // Gemini conversation that updates ProjectInputs
    }),
})
```

